wiki.summary: “Jerry Sprunger” is the title of Tory’s previously teased collaboration with the auto-tune legend himself, T-Pain, and lead single off Chixtape 5. Bearing similarities with the name, Tory Lanez sampled T-Pain’s 2005 hit single, “I’m Sprung”. “Jerry Sprunger” was initially previewed in Miami alongside T-Pain through Twitter, on December 6, 2018, the 13th anniversary of T-Pain’s debut album, Rappa Ternt Sanga. The name of the song also plays off the name of famous television personality, Gerald Norman “Jerry” Springer. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: “Jerry Sprunger” is the title of Tory’s previously teased collaboration with the auto-tune legend himself, T-Pain, and lead single off Chixtape 5. Bearing similarities with the name, Tory Lanez sampled T-Pain’s 2005 hit single, “I’m Sprung”. “Jerry Sprunger” was initially previewed in Miami alongside T-Pain through Twitter, on December 6, 2018, the 13th anniversary of T-Pain’s debut album, Rappa Ternt Sanga. The name of the song also plays off the name of famous television personality, Gerald Norman “Jerry” Springer. This song was heavily previewed on Tory’s Instagram Live and also on T-Pain’s stories before being released one week before Chixtape 5. Read more on Last.fm.
